
00:00:01,502 --> 00:00:02,736
NARRATOR:
Tonight, by popular demand,

00:00:02,736 --> 00:00:05,739
it's a very special
young-entrepreneur episode

00:00:05,739 --> 00:00:09,276
of "Shark Tank," where we look
to the future of America.

00:00:09,276 --> 00:00:11,578
I may be young, but I can make
a difference in this world.

00:00:11,578 --> 00:00:15,849
NARRATOR:
Millions of young Americans
are inspired by "Shark Tank,"

00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:18,919
and many feel they can do
as well as the adults.

00:00:18,919 --> 00:00:20,320
HERJAVEC: We treated you

00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:22,489
just like we did anybody
at any age.

00:00:22,489 --> 00:00:23,991
It's real money.
It's real serious.

00:00:23,991 --> 00:00:25,459
Let me show you how it works.

00:00:25,459 --> 00:00:27,995
NARRATOR: Tonight, we give them
a chance to pitch the sharks

00:00:27,995 --> 00:00:30,964
in hopes of getting
an investment to start, grow,

00:00:30,964 --> 00:00:32,499
or save their businesses.

00:00:32,499 --> 00:00:33,901
It's not just for kids.

00:00:33,901 --> 00:00:36,169
I'm in 300 stores in 34 states.

00:00:36,169 --> 00:00:37,738
My parents have taken out
a mortgage.

00:00:37,738 --> 00:00:38,872
D'oh.

00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:40,040
NARRATOR:
They must convince a shark

00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,309
to invest the full amount
they're asking for,

00:00:42,309 --> 00:00:44,111
or they'll walk away
with nothing.

00:00:44,111 --> 00:00:46,213
You have
serious competition.

00:00:46,213 --> 00:00:48,815
$40,000 is
an absolute-nothing burger.

00:00:48,815 --> 00:00:51,251
I immigrated to America
when I was 6 years old.

00:00:51,251 --> 00:00:54,121
I was about to go to the U.S.
Open until I broke my back.

00:00:54,121 --> 00:00:56,223
NARRATOR:
If the sharks hear a good idea,

00:00:56,223 --> 00:00:58,892
they're ready to invest
using their own money.

00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:00,961
What if we gave them 300k?
Are you nuts?

00:01:00,961 --> 00:01:02,696
NARRATOR: And they're willing
to fight each other

00:01:02,696 --> 00:01:04,164
for a piece of the action.

00:01:04,164 --> 00:01:06,033
I'm the only shark that wants
to help the children.

00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:07,301
Oh, my God.

00:01:07,301 --> 00:01:08,468
He just wants
to be a vampire

00:01:08,468 --> 00:01:10,270
that sucks the money
out of other businesses.

00:01:10,270 --> 00:01:11,605
Mark, why don't you just stick
your head in that beehive?

00:01:11,605 --> 00:01:12,739
GREINER: [laughs]

00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:15,375
NARRATOR:
Who are the sharks?

00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:18,512
They're self-made millionaire
and billionaire investors

00:01:18,512 --> 00:01:20,647
who are entrepreneurs
themselves.

00:01:22,049 --> 00:01:24,785
Kevin O'Leary
is a venture capitalist

00:01:24,785 --> 00:01:27,154
who turned a $10,000 loan

00:01:27,154 --> 00:01:31,758
into a software business
worth $4.2 billion.

00:01:32,893 --> 00:01:36,263
Barbara Corcoran went
from waiting tables in Manhattan

00:01:36,263 --> 00:01:38,932
to building the city's
preeminent real-estate empire.

00:01:40,334 --> 00:01:43,503
Robert Herjavec, the son
of an immigrant factory worker,

00:01:43,503 --> 00:01:45,372
is now a technology mogul

00:01:45,372 --> 00:01:49,910
who sold his first internet
companies for over $350 million.

00:01:51,011 --> 00:01:53,413
Lori Greiner, the queen of QVC,

00:01:53,413 --> 00:01:57,484
holds over 100 patents and
has launched over 300 products,

00:01:57,484 --> 00:02:01,288
grossing over a half a billion
dollars in retail sales.

00:02:01,288 --> 00:02:03,323
And Mark Cuban,

00:02:03,323 --> 00:02:05,258
notorious billionaire
entrepreneur, tech guru,

00:02:05,258 --> 00:02:10,076
and the outspoken owner
of the NBA's Dallas Mavericks.

00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:22,609
First into the tank
is an entrepreneur

00:02:22,609 --> 00:02:24,945
with an easier
and more appealing way

00:02:24,945 --> 00:02:26,546
to drink healthy beverages.

00:02:31,251 --> 00:02:33,587
Hello, sharks.
My name is Carter Kostler.

00:02:33,587 --> 00:02:35,622
I'm from Virginia Beach,
Virginia,

00:02:35,622 --> 00:02:37,724
and my company
is the Define Bottle.

00:02:37,724 --> 00:02:39,593
Today, I'm seeking $100,000

00:02:39,593 --> 00:02:42,529
in exchange for 20% equity
in my company.

00:02:42,529 --> 00:02:46,733
There is an epidemic of soda
in our refrigerators.

00:02:46,733 --> 00:02:49,336
Everyone knows these
sugary drinks are bad for you,

00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:52,272
yet the average American
continues to drink

00:02:52,272 --> 00:02:53,807
one or two cans a day.

00:02:53,807 --> 00:02:55,509
You should be grabbing a water,

00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:57,544
but plain water
is just so boring.

00:02:57,544 --> 00:03:00,480
If only there were
a simple and healthy way

00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:02,349
to make water more exciting.

00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:04,384
Oh, that's right, there is.

00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:07,587
Introducing my product,
the Define Bottle,

00:03:07,587 --> 00:03:09,189
a simple and beautiful way

00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:11,258
to take fresh,
fruit-infused water to go.

00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:13,460
Let me show you how it works.

00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:15,228
First thing you're gonna do
is chop up

00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:17,097
your freshly sliced fruit
of your choice.

00:03:17,097 --> 00:03:18,465
Place it in the bottom chamber,

00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:20,267
where there is a refreezable
base piece

00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:21,635
that helps keep your fruit cool.

00:03:21,635 --> 00:03:24,438
Add your strainer piece and your
top chamber and fill with water.

00:03:24,438 --> 00:03:27,274
Notice, when I fill
the Define Bottle up with water,

00:03:27,274 --> 00:03:28,842
the water goes down
into the bottom,

00:03:28,842 --> 00:03:30,777
but the fruit does not rise
to the mouthpiece.

00:03:31,912 --> 00:03:36,149
Add your lid, pop your top,
and you're ready to go.

00:03:36,149 --> 00:03:38,151
After about 15 minutes,

00:03:38,151 --> 00:03:39,986
the water will be infused
by the fruit,

00:03:39,986 --> 00:03:42,222
adding a refreshing hint
of flavor.

00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,223
Clever.

00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:44,458
Now, sharks, I have

00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:45,826
a Define Bottle
for each of you

00:03:45,826 --> 00:03:47,894
filled
with your favorite fruit.

00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:50,464
Okay.
There you go, Robert.

00:03:50,464 --> 00:03:52,232
Thanks, Carter.
No problem.

00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:54,701
And then, Kevin,
we got Mango.

00:03:54,701 --> 00:03:55,969
Yes.
It's your favorite.

00:03:55,969 --> 00:03:57,170
You didn't have any
with garlic?

00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:58,638
Garlic?
For this guy.

00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:00,107
CUBAN:
Garlic kills vampires.

00:04:00,107 --> 00:04:02,242
Oh, wow,
that's great, Carter.

00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,510
KOSTLER:
Congratulations.

00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:06,012
You are doing something
to improve your health.

00:04:06,012 --> 00:04:09,883
I may be young, but that does
not hold be back from knowing

00:04:09,883 --> 00:04:11,918
that I can make a difference
in this world.

00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:13,520
Now I'm looking for a partner

00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,022
to help me transform
the way people hydrate.

00:04:16,022 --> 00:04:18,658
So, sharks,
who wants to help the world

00:04:18,658 --> 00:04:20,794
define what they drink?

00:04:20,794 --> 00:04:22,996
So, Carter,
how young are you?

00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:24,564
I am 15.

00:04:24,564 --> 00:04:25,966
What?
15?!

00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:27,601
Are you kidding?
You look at least 16.

00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:28,802
CUBAN: You look a whole lot
older than 15, Carter.
Really? Well, thank you.

00:04:28,802 --> 00:04:30,337
Absolutely.
Oh, my gosh.

00:04:30,337 --> 00:04:31,938
Did you create this yourself?

00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,473
Yeah, I created it
when I was 13 years old.

00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:35,041
The story is my mom

00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:37,244
got really into the whole
fruit-infused-water scene.

00:04:37,244 --> 00:04:39,045
But whenever my mom
left the house,

00:04:39,045 --> 00:04:41,348
she always grabbed soda
or a juice.

00:04:41,348 --> 00:04:42,649
So, I wanted my mom

00:04:42,649 --> 00:04:44,651
to enjoy those fresh,
fruit-infused water recipes

00:04:44,651 --> 00:04:46,386
when she left the house.

00:04:46,386 --> 00:04:49,389
So, I did some sketches
on a little legal pad,

00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:52,192
and I pitched the idea
to my parents.

00:04:52,192 --> 00:04:53,426
What are your sales?

00:04:53,426 --> 00:04:57,164
We have done $65,000 in sales
since may 15th.

00:04:57,164 --> 00:04:58,198
Wow.

00:04:58,198 --> 00:05:01,368
In 4 months, $65,000?
Yes.

00:05:01,368 --> 00:05:04,471
And was that at wholesale
or at retail?

00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:06,873
Well, 50% of our sales
have been online.

00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:08,308
50% have been wholesale.

00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:11,678
We sold them on our website,
and we have retail accounts.

00:05:11,678 --> 00:05:13,647
Who do you have
as retailers?

00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:15,949
Whole Foods,
Davids Teas in Canada.

00:05:15,949 --> 00:05:17,551
Carter, how did
Davids Tea find you?

00:05:17,551 --> 00:05:18,885
How did Whole Foods
find you?

00:05:18,885 --> 00:05:21,521
I cold-called companies,
so I walked into Whole Foods --

00:05:21,521 --> 00:05:22,722
Like, right at the store?

00:05:22,722 --> 00:05:24,157
Literally, right at the store --

00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,793
walked in, said, "Hey, can I
speak to the produce manager?"

00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:28,662
Shake his hand, looked him
in the eye, and I say,

00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:30,797
"Sir, this product is gonna be
excellent at Whole Foods."

00:05:30,797 --> 00:05:32,065
Love the hustle,
my friend.

00:05:32,065 --> 00:05:33,366
Thank you.

00:05:33,366 --> 00:05:35,535
We got invited to the whole
foods farmers' market,

00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:37,604
and we did $1,000 worth
of bottles in 3 hours.

00:05:37,604 --> 00:05:39,873
Tell me about
the Davids Tea order.

00:05:39,873 --> 00:05:41,308
Is that a firm order?

00:05:41,308 --> 00:05:44,911
Yes, we did a order of 165
bottles, and they all sold out.

00:05:44,911 --> 00:05:46,046
They loved it.

00:05:46,046 --> 00:05:48,615
Okay, and do -- do you have
a reorder from them?

00:05:48,615 --> 00:05:50,550
We don't have a reorder yet.
Why?

00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:52,752
It's -- it's too early, I think.
Why?

00:05:52,752 --> 00:05:54,955
Carter, let me go back
for a second.

00:05:54,955 --> 00:05:57,090
What do you sell it for
at retail,

00:05:57,090 --> 00:05:58,158
and what does it
cost you?

00:05:58,158 --> 00:06:00,227
The retail price
for that bottle is $30,

00:06:00,227 --> 00:06:02,829
and it costs,
to get to our door, $10.

00:06:02,829 --> 00:06:05,732
But we're currently talking
to a manufacturer over in China,

00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:07,000
and they have guaranteed us

00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,236
they can get the price
of this bottle down to $5.

00:06:09,236 --> 00:06:10,237
CUBAN:
What about online?

00:06:10,237 --> 00:06:12,038
Where's your traffic coming
from online?

00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:12,973
Right, yeah, absolutely.

00:06:12,973 --> 00:06:14,207
Well, early on,

00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:17,277
I created fruit-infused-water
recipe websites.

00:06:17,277 --> 00:06:21,147
And my goal was to promote the
Define Bottle on those sites.

00:06:21,147 --> 00:06:22,883
Okay. What kind of traffic
are you getting,

00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:24,551
what kind of conversion
are you getting,

00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:26,253
and what do you know
about your customers?

00:06:26,253 --> 00:06:29,322
Okay, well, we currently get
2,000 hits a day on those sites.

00:06:29,322 --> 00:06:32,025
Okay.
And our conversion rate,
I think it's 0.5.

00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,729
Why do you think your
conversion rate's so low?

00:06:36,997 --> 00:06:38,531
You know, I don't know.

00:06:38,531 --> 00:06:42,135
I have a question, Mark,
that might answer some of this.

00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:43,203
Yes.

00:06:43,203 --> 00:06:44,871
Are you aware of your
competition out there?

00:06:44,871 --> 00:06:46,006
Yes.

00:06:46,006 --> 00:06:47,173
Our biggest competitor,

00:06:47,173 --> 00:06:49,242
they're currently selling
in Brookstone.

00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:51,778
It's big. It's bulky.
It's stainless steel.

00:06:51,778 --> 00:06:55,015
You can't see the fruit like
in the Define Bottle you can.

00:06:55,015 --> 00:06:56,583
And it has little razor blades
on the bottom

00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,418
that require you to mash up
and grind up your fruit.

00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:02,622
The problem is, while it's
very nice and it works well,

00:07:02,622 --> 00:07:07,193
there's a ton of competition
out in the space right now

00:07:07,193 --> 00:07:09,930
with this exact same
kind of thing.

00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:12,632
And they're a lot
less expensive,

00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:15,535
but I think
they also work well.

00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:17,737
For that reason,
I'm out.

00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:19,339
Okay. Thank you.

00:07:20,907 --> 00:07:22,575
How much have you spent
developing it?

00:07:22,575 --> 00:07:24,344
$300,000.

00:07:24,344 --> 00:07:26,012
Wow.
You've got to be kidding.

00:07:26,012 --> 00:07:27,847
My parents have taken out
a mortgage on the house.

00:07:27,847 --> 00:07:29,749
D'oh.

00:07:29,749 --> 00:07:33,153
Wow. This is a big bet
you guys have made.

00:07:34,387 --> 00:07:37,290
I think your product's
so darn pretty,

00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,692
I want to own one.

00:07:38,692 --> 00:07:44,297
But $300,000 for your parents
blows my mind.

00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:48,301
Carter, I think you spent
way too much money

00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:50,837
developing this.
I'd never get my money back.

00:07:50,837 --> 00:07:52,305
I'm out.

00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:55,508
Okay.
Well, thank you.

00:07:55,508 --> 00:07:59,579
O'LEARY:
So, there's a tremendous amount
of competition.

00:07:59,579 --> 00:08:01,781
And in my view,
it's not investable.

00:08:01,781 --> 00:08:03,249
For that reason, I'm out.

00:08:03,249 --> 00:08:06,152
Okay.

00:08:08,722 --> 00:08:10,857
Two sharks left on either end.

00:08:12,559 --> 00:08:14,494
HERJAVEC: Carter,
here's where I'm at.

00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:16,396
This is a beautiful,
beautiful design.

00:08:16,396 --> 00:08:18,765
You've got
some great retailers.

00:08:18,765 --> 00:08:21,835
So, that's all good news.
Here's the bad news.

00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:24,604
You're into a retailer
that gave you a great order,

00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:27,207
and they didn't reorder.
And you don't know why.

00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:29,442
But I like the product.
Thank you.

00:08:29,442 --> 00:08:31,077
We need to do
some research,

00:08:31,077 --> 00:08:33,113
but I'm willing
to make you an offer.

00:08:41,388 --> 00:08:43,289
NARRATOR:
Three sharks are out,

00:08:43,289 --> 00:08:46,226
but Robert is willing
to take a chance.

00:08:46,226 --> 00:08:47,527
I'm willing
to make you an offer.

00:08:48,795 --> 00:08:51,164
I'll give you the $100,000
that you're looking for,

00:08:51,164 --> 00:08:55,869
but because there's risk,
I want 40% of the business.

00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:57,504
Okay.

00:08:57,504 --> 00:09:00,440
Um...Robert, thank you
so much for your offer.

00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,409
Uh, would you mind
if I go in the hallway

00:09:02,409 --> 00:09:04,010
and talk to my parents?

00:09:04,010 --> 00:09:05,245
Well,
there's another shark.
Don't you want to hear what --

00:09:05,245 --> 00:09:06,479
No, go ahead. no, go ahead.
Talk to your parents.

00:09:06,479 --> 00:09:07,781
Don't you want to find out
what Mr. Cuban's doing?

00:09:07,781 --> 00:09:09,716
No, I want him to talk
to his parents first.

00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:10,717
[laughs]

00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:11,885
Okay, thank you.

00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:16,056
Lori, Barbara...
Uh-huh.

00:09:16,056 --> 00:09:17,157
...And Kevin are out.

00:09:17,157 --> 00:09:19,592
Robert is asking for 40%.

00:09:19,592 --> 00:09:21,761
Have you told them
what assets you have yet?

00:09:21,761 --> 00:09:22,796
No, I have not.
It didn't come up yet.

00:09:22,796 --> 00:09:23,797
Should he ask more
to help us out?

00:09:23,797 --> 00:09:25,031
Oh, well, then,
you need to do that.

00:09:25,031 --> 00:09:26,366
That's my opinion that you need
to go back and say...

00:09:26,366 --> 00:09:27,634
They didn't ask.
..."Here's what my --

00:09:27,634 --> 00:09:29,069
and here's what
the company is worth."

00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:30,370
Mark,
what are you thinking?

00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:32,572
At 15,
when I had my businesses,

00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:34,641
I could walk into anywhere.
No one's gonna say no.

00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:36,443
Everybody's always gonna
give you a chance.

00:09:36,443 --> 00:09:37,811
Right, no one's gonna be
mean to a kid.

00:09:37,811 --> 00:09:40,914
So, there's a balance between
what's real and sustainable

00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:42,148
by the product itself

00:09:42,148 --> 00:09:45,085
and what's just the carry
of him being a kid.

00:09:45,085 --> 00:09:46,286
But I don't know that.

00:09:46,286 --> 00:09:48,221
But that said,
it's a cool product.

00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:53,626
Carter, welcome back.

00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:57,597
So, the offer was $100,000
for 40%.

00:09:57,597 --> 00:10:02,102
Right. My parents and I
discussed it out there,

00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:05,638
and we think that our company is
worth a little more than that.

00:10:05,638 --> 00:10:06,973
We -- we have assets.

00:10:06,973 --> 00:10:12,212
We have $85,000 in tooling,
150 grand in inventory.

00:10:12,212 --> 00:10:15,281
We have sales of $65,000
since May 15th,

00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:18,118
projected sales of $200,000
this year,

00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:20,320
$400,000 in sales next year.

00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:22,355
Carter, what do you think
it's worth?

00:10:22,355 --> 00:10:25,125
Uh, $500,000.

00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:30,964
So, you are not going to take
his offer of $100,000 for 40%.

00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:32,198
That's what I hear.

00:10:32,198 --> 00:10:35,935
Well, Robert, would you
be willing to do 30%?

00:10:39,172 --> 00:10:41,741
It's like I said.
We have assets.

00:10:41,741 --> 00:10:43,543
Carter, the assets
are only worth something

00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:44,844
if the company
is successful.

