00:31:09,701 --> 00:31:11,803
and I live on my family farm
in Deming, Washington.

00:31:11,803 --> 00:31:14,239
I've learned a lot
about running my business

00:31:14,239 --> 00:31:15,507
by being on the farm.

00:31:15,507 --> 00:31:18,043
I've built fences,
cleaned up after the animals,

00:31:18,043 --> 00:31:19,010
and I feed them.

00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:20,512
And sometimes, you just got

00:31:20,512 --> 00:31:22,147
to put a little bit
of elbow grease into it.

00:31:24,616 --> 00:31:25,984
I really like bees

00:31:25,984 --> 00:31:29,121
because they get so much hate
from a lot of people.

00:31:29,121 --> 00:31:30,822
Bees all around the world

00:31:30,822 --> 00:31:33,825
are suffering from
colony collapse disorder.

00:31:33,825 --> 00:31:35,127
Colony collapse disorder

00:31:35,127 --> 00:31:37,329
is a mysterious disease
that will infect the hive,

00:31:37,329 --> 00:31:39,898
and it's very hard
to find the exact cause.

00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:41,099
I started this company

00:31:41,099 --> 00:31:43,335
to help save the bees
and my family farm.

00:31:43,335 --> 00:31:45,804
My mom calls me
an eco-entrepreneur.

00:31:47,672 --> 00:31:49,941
There's nothing
like my product in stores.

00:31:49,941 --> 00:31:52,277
I created a new category
for honey to be in

00:31:52,277 --> 00:31:53,478
that could change the world.

00:31:53,478 --> 00:31:56,281
If we don't get an investment
from the sharks,

00:31:56,281 --> 00:31:58,116
I feel that we may lose
our farm.

00:31:58,116 --> 00:32:00,252
My mom and dad
have been funneling money

00:32:00,252 --> 00:32:01,686
out of their retirement fund

00:32:01,686 --> 00:32:03,321
and putting it
into the business,

00:32:03,321 --> 00:32:04,556
and I feel like it's my job

00:32:04,556 --> 00:32:06,792
to make this business
succeed for them.

00:32:17,436 --> 00:32:19,004
CORCORAN:
I hope there's no bees.

00:32:19,004 --> 00:32:20,305
[gasps]

00:32:20,305 --> 00:32:21,706
Ooh.
Creepy.

00:32:23,809 --> 00:32:25,777
Oh, wow.

00:32:25,777 --> 00:32:26,978
Hi, sharks.

00:32:26,978 --> 00:32:28,113
[laughs]

00:32:28,113 --> 00:32:29,381
CUBAN: [laughs]

00:32:29,381 --> 00:32:31,349
My name is Henry Miller.
I'm from Deming, Washington,

00:32:31,349 --> 00:32:33,785
and I'm seeking $150,000

00:32:33,785 --> 00:32:37,355
for a 25% stake of my incredible
company, Henry's Humdingers,

00:32:37,355 --> 00:32:39,791
the natural condiment,
honey with a kick.

00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:42,160
It all started back
when I was 11 years old,

00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:44,396
and I sat next to a beekeeper
on a plane.

00:32:44,396 --> 00:32:46,832
And I learned about
colony collapse disorder.

00:32:46,832 --> 00:32:49,801
Did you know that if all the
bees died, within seven years,

00:32:49,801 --> 00:32:51,837
the whole food chain
would collapse?

00:32:51,837 --> 00:32:53,371
The unthinkable would happen.

00:32:53,371 --> 00:32:55,740
Mr. Wonderful, you wouldn't be
able to make any more money.

00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:57,108
Don't worry.
I speak bee.

00:32:57,108 --> 00:32:58,610
[laughter]

00:32:58,610 --> 00:33:01,413
Anyhow, I asked my parents for
a beehive for my 12th birthday,

00:33:01,413 --> 00:33:03,248
and what do you know?
They got me one.

00:33:03,248 --> 00:33:05,450
Next thing you know,
I had so much sweet honey,

00:33:05,450 --> 00:33:07,085
I didn't know
what to do with it.

00:33:07,085 --> 00:33:09,554
So, I started selling it
on the side of the road.

00:33:09,554 --> 00:33:11,423
And I realized
I need to be different.

00:33:11,423 --> 00:33:13,825
There's so many people out there
selling sweet honey

00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:15,760
that it just needed to change.

00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:17,963
And that's how
Henry's Humdingers was born.

00:33:17,963 --> 00:33:22,100
And I turned beekeeping
into a business.

00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:23,235
And I went from...

00:33:23,235 --> 00:33:24,603
[Southern accent]
Henry's Humdingers...

00:33:24,603 --> 00:33:26,738
[laughter]

00:33:26,738 --> 00:33:28,940
[normal voice]
...To Henry's Humdingers LLC.

00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:31,710
I take this ancient thing
like honey,

00:33:31,710 --> 00:33:34,913
and I flip it upside down
by adding spices to it.

00:33:34,913 --> 00:33:37,983
It's good in meatloaf,
over chicken, ice cream,

00:33:37,983 --> 00:33:40,218
and even martinis --
so I've been told.

00:33:40,218 --> 00:33:42,287
I brought some samples
for you all to try.

00:33:47,459 --> 00:33:48,860
Thanks, Henry.

00:33:48,860 --> 00:33:50,061
No problem.

00:33:50,061 --> 00:33:51,496
I love the names.

00:33:51,496 --> 00:33:53,765
Yep, I currently
have four flavors.

00:33:53,765 --> 00:33:56,868
There's Grumpy Grandpa,
Naughty Nana,

00:33:56,868 --> 00:33:59,871
Phoebe's Fireball,
and Diabolical Dad.

00:33:59,871 --> 00:34:02,541
Henry, the Diabolical Dad
is fantastic.

00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:04,309
Naughty Nana is, like --
We've made a cheesecake
out of that.

00:34:04,309 --> 00:34:05,477
Wow.

00:34:05,477 --> 00:34:07,178
Are there other
flavored honeys out there?

00:34:07,178 --> 00:34:09,281
There are other
sweet-flavored honeys,

00:34:09,281 --> 00:34:12,217
but I have not encountered
another spicy-flavored honey.

00:34:12,217 --> 00:34:13,184
Where are you selling?

00:34:13,184 --> 00:34:14,819
What retailers are you
in right now?

00:34:14,819 --> 00:34:18,390
Right now, I'm in 300-plus
stores in 34 states,

00:34:18,390 --> 00:34:20,892
and I'm in big distributors,
such as unify east.

00:34:20,892 --> 00:34:22,827
Wow.
And I was in unify west.

00:34:22,827 --> 00:34:24,195
What are your sales?

00:34:24,195 --> 00:34:27,299
My sales -- in the past three
years that I've been --

00:34:27,299 --> 00:34:29,167
been in business, I had $67,000.

00:34:29,167 --> 00:34:30,602
$67,000?
Yeah.

00:34:30,602 --> 00:34:31,670
What about
the last 12 months, Henry?

00:34:31,670 --> 00:34:34,239
Probably about $50,000, I think.

00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:35,974
Henry, you've been at this
for three years.

00:34:35,974 --> 00:34:37,342
You're in 300 stores.

00:34:37,342 --> 00:34:39,978
$50,000
in the past 12 months.

00:34:39,978 --> 00:34:41,880
Don't you think
they should be higher

00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:44,049
given the amount of time
you've put into it?

00:34:44,049 --> 00:34:46,418
The main problem is
I don't have the capital.

00:34:46,418 --> 00:34:47,485
That's why I'm here.

00:34:47,485 --> 00:34:48,653
Got it.

00:34:48,653 --> 00:34:50,221
HERJAVEC: Tell me about
the business today.

00:34:50,221 --> 00:34:51,489
Who's running
this business?

00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:52,958
I mean, obviously,
you didn't drop out of school.

00:34:52,958 --> 00:34:56,127
My mom and dad are both working
at it while I'm at school.

00:34:56,127 --> 00:34:58,430
I make a lot
of the executive decisions.

00:34:58,430 --> 00:35:00,799
My mom's working full-time.

00:35:00,799 --> 00:35:02,801
She gets paid in love
and teenaged angst.

00:35:02,801 --> 00:35:04,235
Did you mention
how much money

00:35:04,235 --> 00:35:05,337
your parents
put in the business?

00:35:05,337 --> 00:35:06,371
I'm sorry.
I don't think I --

00:35:06,371 --> 00:35:08,640
They have put $150,000.

00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:10,542
One of my good friends

00:35:10,542 --> 00:35:14,012
is the largest honey provider
in Canada.

00:35:14,012 --> 00:35:15,347
It's a massive operation.

00:35:15,347 --> 00:35:17,716
He's already got
the distribution and so on.

00:35:17,716 --> 00:35:20,151
How do you compete
with something like that?

00:35:20,151 --> 00:35:22,320
People who have those
large-scale honey things,

00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:23,788
they don't want to have to go in

00:35:23,788 --> 00:35:25,824
and clean all of our spices out
every time

00:35:25,824 --> 00:35:27,492
so they can do
their clean honey run.

00:35:27,492 --> 00:35:28,927
So, just so I'm clear,

00:35:28,927 --> 00:35:31,496
I can't go to
an existing honey company

00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:32,764
and add spices to it.

00:35:32,764 --> 00:35:34,466
It would be very expensive.

00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:36,001
But, Henry,
is there a possibility

00:35:36,001 --> 00:35:38,403
the reason that none of the big
honey guys have done this

00:35:38,403 --> 00:35:41,106
is the market is actually
very small for spiced honey?

00:35:41,106 --> 00:35:44,075
We need more, like,
consumer education.

00:35:44,075 --> 00:35:45,810
That's what a lot of this
will go towards

00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:47,445
because people need to know
what it is.

00:35:47,445 --> 00:35:48,947
It's not a sweetener.
It's a condiment.

00:35:48,947 --> 00:35:51,883
So, you want me to help educate
America about spices

00:35:51,883 --> 00:35:53,551
and garlic in honey when maybe
they don't want to know.

00:35:53,551 --> 00:35:54,986
See, the thing about Kevin --
He has no concept

00:35:54,986 --> 00:35:56,688
of opening up a new category
and creating a new business.

00:35:56,688 --> 00:35:57,956
He just wants to be
a vampire

00:35:57,956 --> 00:35:59,791
that sucks the money
out of other businesses.

00:35:59,791 --> 00:36:01,292
You know, you can say that,

00:36:01,292 --> 00:36:03,395
but the truth is,
I think I'm right.

00:36:03,395 --> 00:36:06,264
I don't think people want,
in a large scale,

00:36:06,264 --> 00:36:07,699
to buy honey with garlic in it

00:36:07,699 --> 00:36:09,868
or honey with jalapeo peppers
in it.
Then just go out.

00:36:12,604 --> 00:36:14,172
Do you have
your own website?
MILLER: Yes.

00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:15,707
Are you doing any type
of marketing

00:36:15,707 --> 00:36:17,108
to drive people
to your website?

00:36:17,108 --> 00:36:18,977
I go to food shows
a lot of the time.

00:36:18,977 --> 00:36:22,747
My first food show I went to
was national expo west.

00:36:22,747 --> 00:36:26,084
I went there, and afterwards
Wegmans called me.

00:36:26,084 --> 00:36:27,752
Are you in Wegmans?

00:36:27,752 --> 00:36:29,654
Yeah, I -- Wegmans has reordered
three times now.

00:36:29,654 --> 00:36:31,222
O'LEARY: So, Henry,
I look at it this way.

00:36:31,222 --> 00:36:34,693
This is a very small category,
so if this takes off,

00:36:34,693 --> 00:36:37,395
the big honey guys
can also add spices to honey.

00:36:37,395 --> 00:36:39,097
They already have
the shelf space,

00:36:39,097 --> 00:36:41,166
and they'll crush you
like the bee you are.

00:36:41,166 --> 00:36:42,567
Unfortunately, for you,

00:36:42,567 --> 00:36:45,103
I'm the only shark that tells
the truth all of the time.

00:36:46,971 --> 00:36:49,207
You're about to hear everybody
give you lots of encouragement,

00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:51,476
but I don't think they're gonna
write you a check for $150,000.

00:36:51,476 --> 00:36:52,544
I'm out.

00:36:52,544 --> 00:36:55,146
All right. Thank you.

00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:56,781
What a nice guy.

00:36:56,781 --> 00:36:58,283
What's wrong
with encouragement?

00:36:58,283 --> 00:37:00,218
If you're encouraging him
to pursue something

00:37:00,218 --> 00:37:02,554
that will never make him money,
you're actually the devil.

00:37:02,554 --> 00:37:06,224
[laughs] We all know
where you're from.

00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:07,358
Hey, I tell the truth.

00:37:07,358 --> 00:37:09,260
I am the angel on his shoulder.

00:37:11,396 --> 00:37:14,933
I think it's great
that you are enterprising,

00:37:14,933 --> 00:37:18,470
that you are caring about bees
and our ecology.

00:37:18,470 --> 00:37:22,707
But my personal opinion is
it's very difficult

00:37:22,707 --> 00:37:26,644
to sell something spicy
like this with honey

00:37:26,644 --> 00:37:29,214
when I think most people

00:37:29,214 --> 00:37:31,683
probably do like
just plain honey.

00:37:31,683 --> 00:37:32,784
Mm.

00:37:32,784 --> 00:37:34,819
So, my opinion is

00:37:34,819 --> 00:37:37,756
this will be a hard --
a hard trek.

00:37:37,756 --> 00:37:41,192
I'm not sure I would get
back the $150,000,

00:37:41,192 --> 00:37:43,995
and so, for that reason,
I'm out.

00:37:43,995 --> 00:37:46,965
Okay.
Thank you for listening.

00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:51,102
Well, I find you
so adorable, Henry.

00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:52,437
You're almost irresistible.

00:37:52,437 --> 00:37:54,773
I think people are gonna
fall for you,

00:37:54,773 --> 00:37:57,475
and I think you shouldn't
get a partner here.

00:37:57,475 --> 00:37:59,911
I think you should go
and do some crowdfunding.

00:37:59,911 --> 00:38:01,246
You do your pitch online,

00:38:01,246 --> 00:38:03,381
you're gonna get all the money
you need.

00:38:03,381 --> 00:38:04,983
I'm out because I think
you have a long road,

00:38:04,983 --> 00:38:06,151
but I don't think
you need me,

00:38:06,151 --> 00:38:07,585
and I don't think
you need anybody here.

00:38:10,455 --> 00:38:11,956
Let me tell you
where I'm at.

00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:14,592
I mean, gosh, if there's a
business I know a lot about --

00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:16,928
I wish you, me, and my friend
could sit in a room

00:38:16,928 --> 00:38:18,797
'cause I'm fascinated
by this product.

00:38:18,797 --> 00:38:20,732
Robert, before you go out,
let me throw something by you.

00:38:31,910 --> 00:38:33,778
NARRATOR:
Three sharks are out,

00:38:33,778 --> 00:38:36,347
but Henry has two more chances
to make a deal.

00:38:36,347 --> 00:38:37,949
HERJAVEC: Let me tell you
where I'm at.

00:38:37,949 --> 00:38:40,685
I mean, gosh, if there's a
business I know a lot about --

00:38:40,685 --> 00:38:43,054
I wish you, me, and my friend
could sit in a room

00:38:43,054 --> 00:38:44,956
'cause I'm fascinated
by this product.

00:38:44,956 --> 00:38:47,192
